Best fast food joint at More Supermarket!
Have tried almost all the varieties available here. Chicken cheese shwarma is the best one.
Yesterday tried the falafel, absolutely loved it! thegreedygluttonsgastronomicjourney.wordpress.com
Good Shawerma at the right location. Decent place for a quick grab. Never fails to disappoint the stomach. Was a regular here but with the hike in price, got compelled to look for an alternative.

It's a small shop beside road. I have been there once or twice. They offer a variety of shawarmas that too in a reasonable price. The only thing I didn't like that the chicken stuffing was a bit too oily.
I had the chicken shawarma . It was delicious with gud filling and all around perfect . The mayonaise was gud in taste . One of the best shawarma i had  . .
Shawarma here was not that tasty. It was had just the taste of mayonnaise. Chicken was not much cooked. It's just a kiosk but adequate seating was provided.

Had taken chicken and veg shawarma.
Chicken was anytime better than the veg one. Stuffing was generous. The white sauce aka mayonnaise used was a little less and hence it tasted better.
Must try for choti-choti bhuk.

We ordered the food online .
Taste is good but the filling is less even in special shawarma !
A good thick filling would be really awesome and more dressing as well !

Better than most of other shawarma shops. I have a big complain from Hyderabadi Shawarma shops, why don't you guys heat the chopped chicken slices properly and why not give cheese sauce with it. Also, who adds onion and cabbage in chicken shawarma.
I am from Delhi and 'Al Bake' can be called as 'Madina' of Shawarma lovers. Well cooked, well chopped and with ample cheese sauce.
Well about this place, Veg falafal was equally good.
Its a small outlet and can be missed, so keep your eyes on this place.
Easy on pocket and good on stomach. A try is always worthy.

Shawarma Stop & Arabian Delight  Is Located Gachibowli.. Near To More Supermarket, Telecom Nagar Gachibowli Hyderabad.. They serve very gud chicken shawarma's.. Visited them recently n ordered...
Double Chicken Shawarma...
Double Chicken Shawarma is rumali roti is gud with huge mayonnaise n chicken stuffing is tasty n delicious... Prices are reasonable n full value for money quality n quantity is superb

My friend ordered shawarma and momos  from the outlet in the evening .trust me the worst momos ever  .The look n the taste of the momos was horrible .
The shawarma was descent .The taste was good but just coz the momos were so bad that's y the low rating  . 
You can try the shawarma  ....

Tried the Falafel in Rumali. Khubbus was not available that day. 
The falafel were not too fresh but were microwaved. I would prefer more flavour in them. 
The Garlic Mayo was thick enough as to not leak. 
The salad was fresh and the veggies retained a good bite. 
Economically priced.

Its a small stall in gachibowli, located in an area which has many such small food stalls around. We had chicken shawarma roll which was just average in taste. The vegetables inside the wrap was not that fresh and the white sauce also was missing the drooling taste. In a way its ok for a quick bite.
A nice place to just go and hang around with friends at mid night and to taste the famous middle East dish.  Not at all costly and the best part for me is its location from where I stay.
Loved the chicken shawarma.  Simple and tasty. Had this dish the first time and loved it.  Momos are ok. Being from North East can't expect awesome Momos here.
Nice flavors, the wrap was very soft and total hygienic @60rs, You cant expect big at this amount. We will visit again for the other menu to try.

I didn't had much craving for food in dinner, my family wanted to have lite food kind of roll so went to food panda searching for roll home delivery . I found this place for which minimum order was 250, so I ordered 3 double chicken shawarma and 1 plate chicken momo . I got the confirmation of order and it was delivered on time. I started eating the momo 1st didn't like one bit of it. It was pretty bad.
Then ate chicken shawarma which was good taste full chicken and sauce .
I would love again to try shawarma 
Food 3/5
Service 3/5

I have had shawarma from lot of places but I did not find anything great from here. the stuffing was very less although we ordered special chicken shawarma. Even a rating of 1 seems to be over rated in my opinion

There's nothing below 1 on zomato I can rate, in reality I would rate this -5/5. Pathatic would be the only word to describe the shawarms from this place. He's literally selling rumali rotis hardly with chicken filling. And that too half cooked. I have tried out spl chicken shawarma. If some one has it for the first time here u'll not have a shawarma for rest of ur life.
Highly not recommended even if this fellow offers it for free.
Nice one if you are looking for Arabian taste.
Good shawarma to try for.but yes i had better from shawarma in other places. Price is pretty much same as it's in most of the places once in a while good place to go for snacks. Pushkar

Being a shawarma lover was always looking for a good one n tried this place today evening.small kiosk in front of more super market gachibowli.there r both shawarma n momos but I tried only shawarma.
Ordered for spl chicken shawarma which is 70/- ...It's average n I had with rumali roti.he's got options wid bun,kuboos n rumali.Not so hygienic inside n nothing great about the taste.

I stumbled upon this shop last evening on my way to Yosta. There is nothing much of an ambiance .
Its clean , they have a fridge and a microwave that barely functions , but its not something that would drive you a way , but yes eating in is the best option - home delivery isn't . The microwave barely warms the shawarma and will loose heat in 5 mins, complaints about cold food aren't surprising ...
I had the SPL shawarma in roomali roti - quite a mouthful this. Loaded with double chicken and some cucumber and some punchy sauce - Spicy mayo probably not sure. The chicken/marination itself is spicy and leaves your mouth zingy.
All in all - pretty filling and pretty happy if they can keep up consistency thegastronomix.net
A street side stall ..The shawarmas are mediocre... Nothing that great .. But not bad if u want to grab something on the go .. :) .. No place to sit as such.mohdazad.wordpress.com

Never eat their double chicken shawarma. They use a lot of bitter cucumber in it, which makes it really bad.
The special chicken shawarma was still good, but the amount of mayo is really less.
I ordered online and the food was cold, when it was delivered, which made the experience really bad.

Never order online with these fellows. Take a minimum of 2 hours and you have to call them to remind them that you placed an order. 90% of the times, their numbers will be switched off or they don't answer the call.

This place offers a good non-greasy shawarma with a lot of chicken pieces, but less mayo and other heart-burning stuff. Quite a mouthful.¬†
Only drawback is that the home-delivery takes a long loong time, in which the shwarma goes cold. Anyway a prefect snack :)
One of the worst places I have ever had a shwarama from. No hygiene and no taste. Mayo is watery. Very less chicken n adds a lot of cabbage and tomatoes that spoil the taste.

Please don't go and try guys, its the worst shawarma I ate. The mayo there is kind if liquid, they mixed lot of water in mayo and the bread they use is kinda stale one...don't even think if chicken...donno from how many days its there....u get much better shawarmas in toli chowki.
